        New Caledonia, Kavatch [Kaavac], 1973, Rémi Pagu Faale, <a href="../../membres/ozanne.htm">Fran&ccedil;oise Ozanne-Rivierre</a></p>
      <p>This text by M. R&eacute;mi Pagu Faale (Kavatch, 1973) is an observation of the habits of two freshwater gobies: Bac (<em>Eleotris melanosoma</em>) a small broadhead sleeper living in the depths, and Dangem (<em>Awaous guamensis</em>) who prefers to hide under rocks.</p>
